@startuml event-driven-signal-flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Event-Driven Signal Flow (Local + Multiplayer Path)

actor User
participant "Card\n(UI Node)" as Card
participant "CardBuffer /\nScrollContainer" as Buffer
participant "CardManager\n(local rules)" as CM
participant "MultiplayerCardManager\n(sync extension)" as MCM
participant "ConnectionManager\n(signal hub)" as Conn
participant "GDSync" as Sync
participant "LocalServerSignaling\n(web patch path)" as LSS
participant "Signaling Server\n(HTTP/SSE relay)" as Relay
participant "Remote Client" as Remote

== Local Event Path (in-process signals) ==
User -> Card : drag/drop interaction
Card -> Card : _get_drag_data()\nemit card_grabbed(card)
User -> Buffer : drop card on target
Buffer -> CM : emit card_placed_in_slot(card, slot)\nor card_dropped_card_container
CM -> CM : _on_card_placed_in_container() /\n_on_card_placed_in_slot():\nincrement move_count, start timer,\nvalidate sorting order

== Multiplayer Event Path (extends local) ==
CM -> MCM : super() returns to override
MCM -> MCM : determine sync action\n(card_moved / entered_buffer / left_buffer)
MCM -> Sync : GDSync.call_func(\nsync_card_moved, [...])
Sync -> LSS : route packet via patched LocalServer (web)
LSS -> Relay : HTTP broadcast / enqueue
Relay -> Remote : SSE event (game_packet)
Remote -> Remote : apply synchronized state\n(move card, update visibility)

== Lobby/Connection Signal Path ==
Conn -> Sync : subscribe to connected/lobby events\n(GDSync.connected, client_joined, etc.)
Sync -> Conn : emit connected/lobby updates
Conn -> Conn : re-emit via inner Signals class\n(player_joined_lobby, player_list_updated, ...)

note right of Conn
In-process event layer:
decouples UI scenes from
transport implementation details.
The inner Signals class provides
namespaced signal re-emission.
end note

@enduml

